  <title>Error Analysis of Digital Communications</title>
  <metadata>
  <md:content-id>m31814</md:content-id><md:title>Error Analysis of Digital Communications</md:title>
  <md:abstract>In this module, we first introduce the eye diagram and constellation diagram as qualitative ways of evaluating the symbol error probability of a digital communication system.  We discuss various symbol alphabets, such as QAM, PAM, and PSK, and their associated decision regions.
Finally, we derive the symbol error probability for PAM and QAM in additive white Gaussian noise, using the Q and erfc functions, and discuss Gray coding.</md:abstract>
  <md:uuid>d4559051-c696-4592-a0e7-b84db6a9b2d7</md:uuid>
</metadata>
